oai_dc:dc.dc:title: SHOALING OF CNOIDAL WAVES
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Svendson, I.A.
Brink-Kjaer, O.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: shoaling
cnoidal waves
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: An equation is derived which governs the propagation of a cnoidal wave train over a gently sloping bottom. The equation is solved numerically, the solution being tabulated in terms of fH (Eq. 47) as a function of Ei = (Etr/pg) 1/3/gT2 and hi = h/gT2. Results are compared with sinusoidal wave theory. Two numerical examples are included.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 13 (1972): Proceedings of 13th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Vancouver, Canada, 1972.; 18
